%description:

Protocol Test Framework -- example opp_test wrapper (fault injection / MITM).

Runs the `tcp_retransmit` program on the MITM demo network: a PacketTap spliced on the wire
drops host1's first TCP data segment (driven by the program's intercept(...) clause), and
the test asserts that host1 retransmits the same segment (same sequence number) after the
retransmission timeout. Passes when the framework prints
"PROTOCOLTEST tcp_retransmit: PASS".

Shows a fault-injection ProtocolTest wrapped as a `.test` case. The tap is a sibling module
in the network; the program names it ("tap") and the ProtocolTester installs the drop rule
at startup, so no tap parameters are needed here.

%extraargs: -l ../lib/libprotocoltest.so -n ../../../src;../lib

%inifile: omnetpp.ini

[General]
network = ProtocolTestMitmDemo
sim-time-limit = 8s
seed-set = 0

# host1 -> host2 TCP, with a PacketTap (module "tap") spliced on the Ethernet link.
*.host1.numApps = 1
*.host1.app[0].typename = "TcpSessionApp"
*.host1.app[0].connectAddress = "host2"
*.host1.app[0].connectPort = 1000
*.host1.app[0].tOpen = 0.1s
*.host1.app[0].tSend = 0.2s
*.host1.app[0].sendBytes = 100B
*.host1.app[0].tClose = -1s
*.host2.numApps = 1
*.host2.app[0].typename = "TcpEchoApp"
*.host2.app[0].localPort = 1000
*.host*.ipv4.arp.typename = "GlobalArp"

*.tester.testName = "tcp_retransmit"

%contains: stdout
PROTOCOLTEST tcp_retransmit: PASS
